# Question 1: Did self-esteem improve over time by diet?
# Data source: selfesteem: The dataset contains 10 individuals’ self-esteem score at three time points during a specific diet
# Methods should include One factor repeated measure ANOVA time effect, Greenhouse-Geisser or Huynh-Feldt correction for sphericity and pairwise comparisons

library(tidyverse)
library(ggpubr)
library(rstatix)

selfesteem <- selfesteem %>%
  gather(key = "time", value = "score", t1, t2, t3) %>%
  convert_as_factor(id, time)
head(selfesteem)
## # A tibble: 6 × 3
##   id    time  score
##   <fct> <fct> <dbl>
## 1 1     t1     4.01
## 2 2     t1     2.56
## 3 3     t1     3.24
## 4 4     t1     3.42
## 5 5     t1     2.87
## 6 6     t1     2.05
# summary stats
selfesteem %>%
group_by(time) %>%
get_summary_stats(score, type = "mean_sd")
## # A tibble: 3 × 5
##   time  variable     n  mean    sd
##   <fct> <fct>    <dbl> <dbl> <dbl>
## 1 t1    score       10  3.14 0.552
## 2 t2    score       10  4.93 0.863
## 3 t3    score       10  7.64 1.14
bxp <- ggboxplot(selfesteem, x = "time", y = "score", add = "point")
bxp

ggqqplot(selfesteem, "score", facet.by = "time")

score.aov <- anova_test(data = selfesteem, dv = score, wid = id, within = time)
score.aov
## ANOVA Table (type III tests)
## 
## $ANOVA
##   Effect DFn DFd      F        p p<.05   ges
## 1   time   2  18 55.469 2.01e-08     * 0.829
## 
## $`Mauchly's Test for Sphericity`
##   Effect     W     p p<.05
## 1   time 0.551 0.092      
## 
## $`Sphericity Corrections`
##   Effect  GGe      DF[GG]    p[GG] p[GG]<.05   HFe      DF[HF]    p[HF]
## 1   time 0.69 1.38, 12.42 2.16e-06         * 0.774 1.55, 13.94 6.03e-07
##   p[HF]<.05
## 1         *
# pairwise comparisons
pwc <- selfesteem %>%
  pairwise_t_test(
    score ~ time, paired = TRUE,
    p.adjust.method = "bonferroni"
    )
pwc
## # A tibble: 3 × 10
##   .y.   group1 group2    n1    n2 statistic    df           p p.adj p.adj.signif
## * <chr> <chr>  <chr>  <int> <int>     <dbl> <dbl>       <dbl> <dbl> <chr>       
## 1 score t1     t2        10    10     -4.97     9 0.000772     2e-3 **          
## 2 score t1     t3        10    10    -13.2      9 0.000000334  1e-6 ****        
## 3 score t2     t3        10    10     -4.87     9 0.000886     3e-3 **
pwc <- pwc %>% add_xy_position(x = "time")
bxp +stat_pvalue_manual(pwc)

# Question 2: An experiment was conducted to look at treatment for depression. Two groups of patients (1: control / 2: treatment) have been followed at four different times (0: pre-test, 1: one month post-test, 3: 3 months follow-up and 6: 6 months follow-up). The dependent variable is a depression score.
# Data source: depression
# Methods should include data summary and visualization, checks for normality, Two factor repeated measure ANOVA, Greenhouse-Geisser or Huynh-Feldt correction for sphericity and pairwise comparison. Don’t forget to give a conclusion

head(depression)
## # A tibble: 6 × 6
##   id    treatment    t0    t1    t2    t3
##   <fct> <fct>     <dbl> <dbl> <dbl> <dbl>
## 1 1     ctr         296   175   187   242
## 2 2     ctr         376   329   236   126
## 3 3     ctr         309   238   150   173
## 4 4     ctr         222    60    82   135
## 5 5     ctr         150   271   250   266
## 6 6     ctr         316   291   238   194
depression <- depression %>%
  gather(key = "time", value = "score", t0, t1, t2, t3) %>%
  convert_as_factor(id, time)
head(depression)
## # A tibble: 6 × 4
##   id    treatment time  score
##   <fct> <fct>     <fct> <dbl>
## 1 1     ctr       t0      296
## 2 2     ctr       t0      376
## 3 3     ctr       t0      309
## 4 4     ctr       t0      222
## 5 5     ctr       t0      150
## 6 6     ctr       t0      316
# summary stats
depression %>%
group_by(treatment,time) %>%
get_summary_stats(score, type = "mean_sd")
## # A tibble: 8 × 6
##   treatment time  variable     n  mean    sd
##   <fct>     <fct> <fct>    <dbl> <dbl> <dbl>
## 1 ctr       t0    score       12 304.   79.1
## 2 ctr       t1    score       12 257.  108. 
## 3 ctr       t2    score       12 216.   76.5
## 4 ctr       t3    score       12 197.   71.7
## 5 treated   t0    score       12 280.   69.6
## 6 treated   t1    score       12  94.5  47.6
## 7 treated   t2    score       12 100.   58.0
## 8 treated   t3    score       12 107.   55.8
bxp <- ggboxplot(depression, x = "time", y = "score", color="treatment",add = "point")
bxp

ggqqplot(depression, "score", facet.by = c("treatment","time"))

# two-factor-repeated measures anova
score.aov2 <- anova_test(data = depression, dv = score, wid = id, within = time, between = treatment)
score.aov2 
## ANOVA Table (type II tests)
## 
## $ANOVA
##           Effect DFn DFd      F        p p<.05   ges
## 1      treatment   1  22 17.886 3.45e-04     * 0.330
## 2           time   3  66 37.615 2.71e-14     * 0.402
## 3 treatment:time   3  66  7.164 3.09e-04     * 0.113

##           Effect    W     p p<.05
## 1           time 0.49 0.012     *
## 2 treatment:time 0.49 0.012     *
##

## 2 treatment:time 0.73 2.19, 48.19 1.00e-03         * 0.814 2.44, 53.73 8.78e-04
##   p[HF]<.05
## 1         *
## 2         *
# normality test
depression %>%
group_by(treatment,time) %>%
shapiro_test(score)
## # A tibble: 8 × 5
##   treatment time  variable statistic      p
##   <fct>     <fct> <chr>        <dbl>  <dbl>
## 1 ctr       t0    score        0.945 0.572 
## 2 ctr       t1    score        0.918 0.268 
## 3 ctr       t2    score        0.951 0.652 
## 4 ctr       t3    score        0.873 0.0706
## 5 treated   t0    score        0.836 0.0248
## 6 treated   t1    score        0.953 0.680 
## 7 treated   t2    score        0.957 0.734 
## 8 treated   t3    score        0.932 0.398
# pairwise comparisons
pwc <- depression %>%
  pairwise_t_test(
    score ~ time, paired = TRUE,
    p.adjust.method = "bonferroni"
    )
pwc
## # A tibble: 6 × 10
##   .y.   group1 group2    n1    n2 statistic    df         p   p.adj p.adj.signif
## * <chr> <chr>  <chr>  <int> <int>     <dbl> <dbl>     <dbl>   <dbl> <chr>       
## 1 score t0     t1        24    24     5.67     23   8.95e-6 5.37e-5 ****        
## 2 score t0     t2        24    24     8.03     23   4.05e-8 2.43e-7 ****        
## 3 score t0     t3        24    24     6.69     23   7.97e-7 4.78e-6 ****        
## 4 score t1     t2        24    24     1.79     23   8.6 e-2 5.18e-1 ns          
## 5 score t1     t3        24    24     1.34     23   1.93e-1 1   e+0 ns          
## 6 score t2     t3        24    24     0.421    23   6.78e-1 1   e+0 ns
# Effect of treatment at each timepoint
one.way <- depression %>%
  group_by(time) %>%
  anova_test(dv = score, wid = id, between = treatment) %>%
  get_anova_table() %>%
  adjust_pvalue(method = "bonferroni")
one.way

# in conclusion, there is a significant (p < 0.05) effect of treatment at t1,t2, and t3.
